  "prompt": "How do I report a bug/loophole on Quora? What will I get for that?",
  "response": "To report a bug or loophole on Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Access the Help Center**:  \n   Visit the [Quora Help Center](https://help.quora.com/hc/en-us).\n\n2. **Submit a Bug Report**:  \n   - Scroll down to the **\"Contact Us\"** section and click on it.  \n   - Fill out the form with details about the bug or loophole you\u2019ve encountered. Be as specific as possible, including steps to reproduce the issue, screenshots, or any other relevant information.  \n   - Choose the appropriate category (e.g., \"Bug\" or \"Technical Issue\") when submitting the form.  \n\n3. **Email Support**:  \n   Alternatively, you can send an email directly to Quora\u2019s support team at **support@quora.com** with details about the issue.\n\n### What You Might Get for Reporting a Bug or Loophole:\nQuora does not have a formal bug bounty program like some other platforms (e.g., Google or Facebook). However, reporting a bug or loophole may be appreciated by the Quora team, especially if it helps improve the platform\u2019s security or functionality. In some cases, they may acknowledge your contribution, but there is no guarantee of rewards or compensation.\n\nIf you\u2019re reporting a significant security vulnerability, you can mention it clearly in your submission, as platforms often take such reports seriously and may respond more promptly. \n\nFor further updates or feedback, keep an eye on your email for responses from Quora\u2019s support team.",
